column5: anyone know what the ice is like on cooch??
Frozen over from aerial shots...but I don't believe it's safe.
Be careful.  We wouldn't want to lose any brothers and sisters to thin ice.  Good luck when you finally do get out there.

Man oh man oh man, I cannot wait for ice on cooch.  I cannot wait for ice anywhere.  I have so many places I wanna fish right now.  I'm not sure if my first Cooch trip this year will be pike or perch ??  I'll figure it out when the time comes I guess.
Couch just froze over.Like Wayne stated,the arieal shots showed that,with still some open spots.Another week folks,and the play grounds should be ready.
When you come home drunk at 1:00 am and you have forgot your wifes birthday again then the ice on cooch is thick enough.  Art

cooch is pretty much my first destination for the ice season as its usually  the first place with safe ice was planning on going sunday but i guess ill wait another week and attack the steelhead instead thanks for  the replies
LOL Roy...you really like to stir the pot....that was hilarious!
